- [ ] 1 Diced Red Onion
- [ ] 1 Diced Red Pepper
- [ ] 2 tbsp Tomato Purée
- [ ] 400g Diced Chicken Breast
- [ ] 3 Diced Bacon Rashers
- [ ] 500ml Chicken Stock
- [ ] 260g Rice
- [ ] 3 Crushed Garlic Cloves
- [ ] 1 Tbsp Barbecue Seasoning 
- [ ] 2-3 Tbsp Barbecue Sauce
- [ ] 120g Grated Mature Cheddar 
- [ ] 1 Tsp Smoked Paprika 
- [ ] 1 Tsp Garlic Granules 
- [ ] 1 Tsp Onion Granules

1. Firstly fry off your onion, and pepper. After a few mins add your garlic and fry for 30 secs.

2. Then add in your chicken & bacon, once your chicken has some colour all over add in the seasonings, tomato purée & BBQ sauce. Give a good mix and cool down the purée.

3. Add in your uncooked rice, stir for another minute or so then add you stock, bring this to a boil. Once boiling, reduce heat to low and cover the pan and leave to cook for 15/20 mins. Stir occasionally!

4. Once the rice is done, scatter the cheese on the top and cover the pan for 1-2 mins then sprinkle some bacon, parsley and green onion.
